{"title": "Unsanitized user input in OS command", "summary": "  Applications should not execute OS commands that are formed from user input. This rule checks for external commands containing user-supplied data. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not execute OS commands that are formed from user input.\nThis rule checks for external commands containing user-supplied data.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid using user input when executing commands:\n\n```php\nexec($_GET[\"command\"]);\n```\n\n\u2705 Use user input indirectly when executing commands:\n\n```php\nif ($_GET[\"action\"] == \"option1\") {\n  $command = \"command1\";\n} else {\n  $command = \"command2\";\n}\n\nexec($command);\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-78"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_exec_using_user_input", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/OS_Command_Injection_Defense_Cheat_Sheet.html"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}